[{"id":"VH992570","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A red laser beam (<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda equals 675 nanometers\"><math alttext=\"lambda equals 675 nanometers\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>675</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.4em\"></mspace><mtext>nm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>) is incident on two very narrow slits that are spaced <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"10 millimeters\"><math alttext=\"10 millimeters\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>10</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.4em\"></mspace><mtext>mm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> apart. The interference pattern is observed on a distant screen. A green laser (<span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lambda equals 500 nanometers\"><math alttext=\"lambda equals 500 nanometers\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>500</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.4em\"></mspace><mtext>nm</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>) is then used instead. Which of the following claims correctly compares characteristics of the dark fringes observed with the green laser to those observed with the red laser?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH992570_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Narrower and farther apart</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Narrower and closer together</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Broader and farther apart</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Broader and closer together</p>"],"answer":1}]